# Skillet Testing Requirements

## Before finishing any code change

1. **Run existing tests** — all must pass:
   ```powershell
   lua tests/run.lua
   ```
   Or: `"C:\Program Files (x86)\Lua\5.1\lua.exe" tests/run.lua` from the addon root.

2. **Add or update tests** when changing testable logic in:
   - [`SkilletUtil.lua`](SkilletUtil.lua) — links, queue aggregation, filters, sort index mapping
   - Any logic extracted to or called through `SkilletUtil`
   - New pure helpers that do not require WoW frames or Ace2

3. **Preserve behavior** — do not remove or weaken tests to make a change pass. Fix the code or update tests only when behavior intentionally changes.

## Where to put tests

| Changed area | Test file |
|---|---|
| Link squish/unsquish, item ID parsing | `tests/test_links.lua` |
| Queue / shopping-list aggregation | `tests/test_queue.lua` |
| Sort index mapping, name comparison | `tests/test_sort.lua` |
| Recipe filter matching | `tests/test_filter.lua` |
| Scan session / cache staleness / progress | `tests/test_cache.lua` |

Shared fixtures: `tests/fixtures/recipes.lua`. WoW API stubs: `tests/wow_mock.lua`.

Prefer testing via `SkilletUtil` (loaded by `tests/run.lua`) rather than duplicating production logic in tests.

## What still needs manual verification

UI, events, queue execution, tooltips, and vendor/bank flows are **not** covered by unit tests. After changes to `UI/`, `Skillet.lua` event handlers, or queue processing, run [`.docs/MANUAL_TEST_CHECKLIST.md`](.docs/MANUAL_TEST_CHECKLIST.md).

Scan-related changes must also satisfy all three primary scan triggers — see [`.cursor/rules/skillet-scan-triggers.mdc`](.cursor/rules/skillet-scan-triggers.mdc).

## Do not ship test artifacts

Never add `tests/`, `luaunit.lua`, or test-only files to [`Skillet-Enhanced.toc`](Skillet-Enhanced.toc).
